{
  "texts": [
    "Here, ⟨•, •⟩ denotes the similarity score between the query and document embeddings, computed as inner product similarity in the shared embedding space.",
    "This dense retrieval stage identifies documents that are semantically similar to the query and provides candidates for grounding the language model's response.",
    "To refine the initial retrieval set R(q), we apply a pre-trained reranker that computes fine-grained relevance scores between the query q and each candidate document d ∈ R(q).",
    "Cross-encoder rerankers are a staple of modern information retrieval and already feature in recent RAG systems (Glass et al., 2022; Wang et al., 2024b).",
    "We therefore deliberately employ an offthe-shelf model."
  ]
}